I agree with the other reviewer, the value here is remarkable. All 4 films individually are hilarious. Beerfest is a gem especially if you enjoyed films like Super Troopers, Major League, Hot Shots, Naked Gun. They all share that silly raunchy humor, but are still light hearted and have an overall "good" vibe thought out the plot. Buy this set while you can!

Part of the Warner's Four Film Series in blu-ray this one is pretty unique because you get all three Harold and Kumar movies and the under appreciated Beerfest in one package.  All the Four Film Series are bare bones, but are the original discs included in the fancier individual sets.
You get extras as they came with the originals in that if it was a one disc set you got the one disc others did and if was a two disc set then you get only the first disc with the movie and maybe some extras, but at this price you can have your Harold and Kumar collection in one pack and Beerfest is pretty darn funny on its own as well...Also you should know that the sets are four separate discs - two to a spindle on each side of the case.  Nothing fancy but blu-rays are not as finicky about being stacked on top of each other as DVDs are.  I own about five of these sets and I haven't had a scratched disc yet.  I don't see a downside here do you???  Not at this price!  I do recommend.

Harold and Kumar have always been a fantastic comedy duo, five stars; but I'd also love to talk about Beerfest. Beerfest is, I believe an underrated gem; made by the same group who made Super Troopers. Beerfest takes a comical turn into the "underground" of Germany's famous Oktoberfest; honestly it's pretty fun seeing these guy's in any film. I'm happy to see these four epic films in one blu ray package. The only downside is the discs are put together in two's, but they are blu ray; so "scratch anxiety" is down. :)
